Mengis Capital Management Inc. Reduces Position in The Priceline Group Inc. (NASDAQ:PCLN)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 

Mengis Capital Management Inc. lowered its position in shares of The Priceline Group Inc. (NASDAQ:PCLN) by 5.6% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor owned 340 shares of the business services provider’s stock after selling 20 shares during the period. Mengis Capital Management Inc.’s holdings in The Priceline Group were worth $605,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
A number of other large investors also recently made changes to their positions in PCLN. BKD Wealth Advisors LLC raised its stake in shares of The Priceline Group by 1.3% in the first quarter. BKD Wealth Advisors LLC now owns 151 shares of the business services provider’s stock worth $269,000 after buying an additional 2 shares during the period. Wrapmanager Inc. raised its position in The Priceline Group by 1.1% in the first quarter. Wrapmanager Inc. now owns 268 shares of the business services provider’s stock worth $477,000 after buying an additional 3 shares during the period. Puplava Financial Services Inc. raised its position in The Priceline Group by 2.7% in the first quarter. Puplava Financial Services Inc. now owns 192 shares of the business services provider’s stock worth $342,000 after buying an additional 5 shares during the period. CAPROCK Group Inc. raised its position in The Priceline Group by 2.5% in the first quarter. CAPROCK Group Inc. now owns 207 shares of the business services provider’s stock worth $368,000 after buying an additional 5 shares during the period. Finally, First Manhattan Co. raised its position in The Priceline Group by 5.3% in the first quarter. First Manhattan Co. now owns 100 shares of the business services provider’s stock worth $147,000 after buying an additional 5 shares during the period. 95.20% of the stock is owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 


 Get The Priceline Group Inc. alerts:



Shares of The Priceline Group Inc. (NASDAQ:PCLN) traded up 0.36% during midday trading on Thursday, hitting $1999.22. The stock had a trading volume of 342,482 shares. The Priceline Group Inc. has a one year low of $1,305.09 and a one year high of $2,008.65. The stock has a market cap of $98.25 billion, a PE ratio of 45.13 and a beta of 1.41. The firm has a 50 day moving average price of $1,887.84 and a 200 day moving average price of $1,759.68. 




The Priceline Group (NASDAQ:PCLN) last released its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, May 9th. The business services provider reported $9.88 EPS for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $8.83 by $1.05. The Priceline Group had a return on equity of 33.94% and a net margin of 20.12%. The business had revenue of $2.42 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $2.45 billion. During the same quarter in the previous year, the firm posted $10.54 earnings per share. The company’s revenue was up 12.6% compared to the same quarter last year. On average, equities analysts forecast that The Priceline Group Inc. will post $73.93 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
